'''Richardson Beach''' is located just outside of [[Hilo]], [[Hawaii]], on the [[Hawaii (island)|Big Island]].  The name Richardson comes from its original owner and builder of the still-standing home there, Robert Richardson. Richardson was a direct descendant of King [[Kamehameha the Great]], and at one time the [[Chief Detective]] of [[Honolulu]] before retiring to Hilo.

Today the beach is a public park, and the home is occupied and operated as the Richardson Ocean Center.

Richardson Beach is the only beach in Hilo with black sand.

