'''Richardson Beach''' is a [[Hawaii County]] park located just outside of [[Hilo]], [[Hawaii]], on the [[Hawaii (island)|Big Island]]. Adjacent is the '''Leleiwi''' beach park.

The name Richardson comes from its original owner and builder of the still-standing home there, Robert Richardson. Richardson was a direct descendant of King [[Kamehameha I]] and at one time the Chief Detective of [[Honolulu]] before retiring to Hilo.
Today the beach is a public park, and the home is occupied and operated as the Richardson Ocean Center.

Richardson Beach is the only beach in Hilo with black sand.

