[[Category:Beaches of Hawaii (island)]]

'''Anaeho{{okina}}omalu Bay''', also known as '''A-Bay''' is a palm fringed beach, shallow water bay located on the [[Kohala, Hawaii|South Kohala]] coast on the island of [[Hawaii (island)|Hawaii]].<ref>http://www.co.hawaii.hi.us/planning/spa/south_kohala/map3.html South Kohala Map</ref> Anaeho{{okina}}omalu is best known for it's sunsets, snorkeling and historic royal fishponds. The nearest town is [[Waikoloa Village, Hawaii|Waikaloa Village]], which used to be owned by [[Parker Ranch]]. The property just North of the beach and fishponds are owned and operated by [[Outrigger Hotels & Resorts]]. <ref>http://www.outrigger.com/hotels-resorts/hawaiian-islands/hawaii-big-island/kolea Official Web site for the Outrigger Kolea</ref> The area is part of the '''Waikoloa Beach Resort''' <ref>http://waikoloabeachresort.com/Waikoloa-Beach-Resort Official Web site for the Waikoloa Beach Resort</ref>

It is the location of the '''Lavaman Triathlon''', one of the qualifying events for the [[Ironman Triathlon]] World Championships. <ref>http://www.lavamantriathlon.com Official Web site for the Lavaman Triathlon</ref>

