{{Hawaii-geo-stub}}

'''Isaac Hale Beach Park''', also known as '''Pohioki''' is an oceanfront park, boat launch and surf location along '''Pohioki Bay''' in the [[Puna district]] of the [[Hawaii (island)|Big Island of Hawaii]]. It is only one of a few places in the Southeast shore of Hawaii that allows for such facilities. Pohioki Bay is known for its strong currents and although the park in known for good snorkeling, conditions are usually not ideal. The park was recently expanded and modernized in 2006.<ref>http://www.hawaii-county.com/parks/isaachale.htm County of Hawaii Parks and Recreation</ref>
