'''Old Kona Airport State Recreation Area''' is a park built on the site of an old airport just North of [[Kailua, Hawaii County, Hawaii]]. The larger [[Kona International Airport]] was built at [[Keahole Point]] in 1970.<ref>[http://www.airfields-freeman.com/HI/Airfields_HI_Hawaii.htm Old Kona Airport] on Abandoned Airfields web site</ref>
The old 3800 foot long runway is now used for a large parking lot and the old terminal building is now a public use pavilion. There are walking trails, restrooms, and picnic facilities.
The 103.7 acres of the old airport now include facilities run by [[Hawaii County, Hawaii|County of Hawai{{okina}}i]].<ref>[http://www.hawaiistateparks.org/parks/hawaii/index.cfm?park_id=55 Old Kona Airport description] on Hawaii State Park web site</ref> These include baseball and soccor fields, the '''Kona Community Aquatic Center''', and '''Kekuaokalani Gym''', located at 75-5530 Kuakini Highway.<ref>[http://www.hawaii-county.com/parks/konaaquaticspool.htm Kona Aquatic Center] Official web site</ref> A 217 acre marine preserve was created in 1992.<ref>[http://hawaii.gov/dlnr/dar/coral/mlcd_old_kona.html Marine Life Conservation District] Official web site</ref>
