'''Kauna{{okina}}oa Bay''' has one of the few white sand beaches of the [[Kohala Coast]], the western side of the [[Hawaii (island)|island of Hawai{{okina}}i]]. A historic hotel is located on the bay.
==Description== The bay is accessed via Mauna Kea Beach Drive, just west of state Route 19, [[Hawaii Belt Road]], at {{coord| 20|0|16|N| 155|49|30|W| display=inline,title |type:landmark_region:US-HI}}, about {{convert|2.6|mi}} south of [[Kawaihae, Hawaii]].<ref>{{gnis|1905422|Kaunaoa Bay}}</ref> A part of the [[Ala Kahakai National Historic Trail]] can be hiked north to [[Samuel M. Spencer Beach Park]] or south to [[Hapuna Beach State Recreation Area]]. Although public restrooms and showers are available, a limited number of parking passes are available at the resort gate.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.co.hawaii.hi.us/planning/spa/south_kohala/map2.html |title= South Kohala map 2 |work=Shoreline access |publisher=on official Hawai{{okina}}i County web site |accessdate=2010-03-30 }}</ref>
==History== The land above the bay is part of the [[Parker Ranch]], owned by [[Richard Smart (actor)|Richard Smart]]. In 1965 Smart leased it for a hotel financed by [[Laurance Rockefeller]]. It is named [[Mauna Kea Beach Hotel]] for the mountain [[Mauna Kea]] which is visible above the bay when not obscured by clouds.<ref>{{cite news |title= Grande dame back in all her glitter |date= March 29, 2009 |newspaper= [[West Hawaii Today]] |author= Chelsea Jensen |url= http://www.westhawaiitoday.com/articles/2009/03/29/local/local01.txt |accessdate= 2010-04-02 }}</ref>
